AGI - "We have reached a political agreement to extend the regime of sanctions against Iran, currently in force for drones, even missiles. For their transfer to Russia. As the regime is extended to other geographical areas, such as the Middle East - it applies to both missiles and drones - and finally the list of prohibited drone components has been expanded". This was announced by the EU High Representative for Foreign Policy, Josep Borrell, at the end of the Foreign Council in Luxembourg.
&nbsp;
<h2>Tajani: "Favorable to new sanctions"</h2>
"We will also discuss the work we have done in the G7 but here we are at Community level, any sanctions to be applied to Iran, especially with regard to the cession of drones and possibly missiles to Houthi, Hezbollah, as well as was done for the sale to the Russian Federation. We are in favour of inflicting these sanctions, we will see what we will discuss, but it was already clear, as far as we are concerned, in the message contained in the G7 document." The Foreign Minister, Antonio Tajani, said this in a press position at the edge of the Foreign Council in Luxembourg, answering a question on the supply of Italian Samp-T to Ukraine.
&nbsp;
<h2> The Ira of Tehran</h2>
Iran has defined the EU's plan to impose new sanctions on the country for the delivery of missiles and drones to Russia and to groups supported by the Middle East regime. "If they undertake any action, it will be recorded as a shameful act in the history of Europe," said Iranian Foreign Ministry spokesman Naser Kananì in a press conference in Tehran.
&nbsp;
<div </div
&nbsp;
The diplomat added that if they sanctioned Tehran "it would be a reward for the aggressor regime and an illegal action against a government that acted only in the framework of laws to create deterrence". The reference is clearly to the bombing of April 1 to the Iranian consulate in Damascus, in which seven members of the revolutionary Guard died, and to the attack of retaliation with hundreds of missiles and drones against Israel, which did not cause damage.
"It is interesting to note that the European Union has not adopted any sanctions against the regime that committed crimes and massacred the Palestinian people, executed sick and injured within hospitals and used the hospital complex as it were common. On the other hand (the EU, ndr) speaks of sanctions against a government that has acted in the international context," said the spokesman.&nbsp;
